Haaphy Dating App Privacy Policy

Last Updated: 4/29/2024

Welcome to Haaphy, the dating app designed to connect people in meaningful relationships. Protecting your privacy and ensuring the security of your personal information is our top priority. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and safeguard your data when you use the Haaphy app.

By using Haaphy, you agree to the terms outlined in this Privacy Policy. Please take the time to read and understand this document. If you have any questions or concerns, feel free to contact us at [contact email].

Information We Collect

Personal Information: When you sign up for Haaphy, we collect personal information such as your name, email address, date of birth, gender, sexual orientation, and other details you choose to provide.
Location Information: With your consent, we may collect your precise location data to offer location-based services, such as finding matches near you or suggesting local events.
Media Information: Haaphy allows you to upload photos and videos to your profile. We collect and store this media content to display on your profile and share with potential matches.
Usage Information: We collect data about how you interact with the app, including your browsing history, app usage patterns, preferences, and device information (such as IP address, device type, operating system, and browser type).
Communication Data: When you communicate with other users through Haaphy's messaging or chat features, we may collect and store the content of those communications to facilitate the exchange and improve our services.
How We Use Your Information

To Provide and Improve Services: We use your information to operate, maintain, and improve Haaphy's features, personalize your experience, and develop new functionalities.
Matching and Recommendations: We use your data, including location and preferences, to match you with potential partners and provide personalized recommendations.
Communication: Your information helps us facilitate communication between users, including messaging, notifications, and updates about matches or events.
Security and Fraud Prevention: We use data to ensure the security of our platform, detect and prevent fraudulent activities, and enforce our Terms of Service.
Marketing and Analytics: With your consent, we may use your information for marketing purposes, such as sending promotional offers, conducting surveys, and analyzing user trends to improve our marketing strategies.
Data Sharing and Disclosure

Third-Party Service Providers: We may share your information with third-party service providers that assist us in operating Haaphy, providing customer support, conducting analytics, or delivering targeted advertisements.
Legal Compliance: We may disclose your information when required by law, legal process, or government request, or to protect the rights, property, or safety of Haaphy, its users, or others.
Business Transfers: In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your information may be transferred to a third party as part of the transaction. We will notify you of any such change and ensure your data continues to be protected.
Data Security

Haaphy employs industry-standard security measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

Your Choices and Rights

Account Settings: You can review and update your account information and privacy settings within the Haaphy app.
Location Services: You can control Haaphy's access to your device's location through your device settings or app permissions.
Marketing Communications: You can opt out of receiving promotional emails or notifications from Haaphy by adjusting your communication preferences.
Data Access and Deletion: You have the right to access, update, or delete your information. Contact us at [contact email] to make such requests.
Children's Privacy

Haaphy is not intended for individuals under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect or solicit personal information from minors. If we become aware that we have inadvertently gathered information from a child, we will take steps to delete it promptly.

Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. We will notify you of any significant changes through the Haaphy app or other means. Your continued use of Haaphy after such changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.

Contact Us

If you have any questions, concerns, or feedback about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at [contact email]. We are committed to addressing your inquiries and resolving any issues promptly.

Thank you for choosing Haaphy. We are dedicated to creating a safe, enjoyable, and respectful environment for our users.

